Yes, mandatory fun is work!

00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:37.580 position:50% align:center
You think I wanted to come to
the company New Year's party?

00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:40.000 position:50% align:center
Don't call me again, dammit!

00:16:40.083 --> 00:16:44.295 position:50% align:center
[KIKAKU panting]

00:16:44.379 --> 00:16:47.298 position:50% align:center
Bet you weren't expecting Uebu
to show up either, were ya?

00:16:47.382 --> 00:16:50.677 position:50% align:center
Wait, you're saying he did?
That is surprising.

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.220 position:50% align:center
You know how it is.

00:16:52.303 --> 00:16:54.389 position:50% align:center
We were the only new
hires for this year,

00:16:54.472 --> 00:16:56.016 position:50% align:center
and us new guys
gotta stick together,

00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:58.768 position:50% align:center
even if it's not always easy
for us to communicate.

00:16:58.852 --> 00:17:00.562 position:50% align:center
Uebu can be kinda stubborn,

00:17:00.645 --> 00:17:03.064 position:50% align:center
but I convinced him
to see reason.

00:17:03.148 --> 00:17:05.859 position:50% align:center
I originally hadn't planned
to come to this function.

00:17:05.942 --> 00:17:08.319 position:50% align:center
But my colleague
smashed my glasses,

00:17:08.403 --> 00:17:10.530 position:50% align:center
and he threatened to send
a bunch of waifu pillows

00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:11.990 position:50% align:center
to my parents' house in my name

00:17:12.073 --> 00:17:14.075 position:50% align:center
if I didn't go to
the company party.

00:17:14.159 --> 00:17:15.744 position:50% align:center
Oh, how very ghastly!

00:17:15.827 --> 00:17:17.412 position:50% align:center
